<L>__{interior special education classroom night later}
<A>__{curtis, samantha, and hannah sit on the floor in a circle atop the colored rug. samantha turns over large flashcards with illustrated scenes on them. they take turns making the corresponding sign. curtis stares at samantha, but she's still giving him the cold shoulder. finally, while holding up a card, she looks at him. he signs, "i'm sorry". a fist moving in a circular motion at his chest.}
<C>__{samantha}
<D>__{you're not sorry.}
<C>__{curtis}
<D>__{i am sorry.}
<A>__{she looks to hannah and signs, "swim".}
<C>__{samantha}
<D>__{well, you stink. you smell really bad.}
<A>__{he smiles.}
<C>__{curtis}
<D>__{i think i smell good.}
<A>__{she smiles, begrudgingly, and then signs to hannah, "dad" and "stink". curtis turns to some ladies behind him.}
<C>__{curtis }
<D>__{do i smell good?}
<A>__{samantha laughs and tries to cover his mouth with her hand.}
<C>__{curtis }
<D>__{see. maybe i should marry her instead.}
<A>__{they continue to laugh.}
<C>__{samantha}
<D>__{stop.}
